File: internal/server/config/config.go
Package: config
Purpose: Declares target configuration model bindings mapping server networks, persistence engines, and external crypto material locations.
Types: Config, ServerConfig, StorageConfig, PKIConfig struct scopes.
Globals: ErrServerBindGRPCEmpty, ErrPostgresDSNEmpty, ErrHTTPBindWithoutACME, ErrServerCAKeyEmpty, ErrDeviceCAKeyEmpty, ErrDeviceCACertEmpty.
Security Constraints: Explicitly decouples transport identity by hosting individual paths for decoupled server-auth and container-issuance private keys.

File: internal/server/config/validate.go
Package: config
Purpose: Evaluates configuration boundaries ensuring zero-knowledge isolation parameters remain active.
Functions:
func (c Config) Validate() error. Purpose: validation runner. Enforces presence of gRPC bind and persistence strings. If ACME/LetsEncrypt domains are unassigned, strictly requires external filesystem locations for ServerCAKeyPath, DeviceCAKeyPath, and DeviceCACertPath to guarantee explicit cryptographic infrastructure boot.
Security Constraints: Prevents runtime operational mode with empty keys when local certificate synthesis is active.

File: internal/server/config/viper.go
Package: config
Purpose: Ties platform environment boundaries, default maps, and YAML files to the unified config registry.
Functions:
func NewViper() *viper.Viper. Purpose: Allocates state, defines GOPHKEEPER_SERVER env namespaces, maps dots to underscores, binds default addresses.
func ReadConfigFile(v *viper.Viper) error. Purpose: Injects runtime YAML parameters if a configuration target path exists.
func LoadFromViper(v *viper.Viper) (Config, error). Purpose: Combines unmarshalling routines with structural validation rules.

File: internal/server/config/config_test.go
Package: config_test
Purpose: Runs verification suites over initialization layers using deterministic mocked environment constraints.
Functions:
TestNewViper_Defaults: Assures baseline defaults load properly.
TestConfig_Validate: Exercises all structural error conditions across invalid setups.
TestLoadFromViper_EnvironmentVariables: Validates automated prefix mappings via t.Setenv strings.
TestReadConfigFile: Spawns ephemeral temporary disk files to guarantee config serialization.
